e</a></li><li><a id="q12" >5 per cent of the population</a></li></ol><br/></li><br/><li id="5">Approximately how many students studied Italian in 1987?<ol class="answerList"><li><a id="q13" >30</a></li><li><a id="q14" >80</a></li><li><a id="q15" >180</a></li></ol><br/></li><br/><li id="6">Between 1997 and 2002 the number of students of Italian (…).<ol class="answerList"><li><a id="q16" >fell</a></li><li><a id="q17" >remained the same</a></li><li><a id="q18" >rose</a></li></ol><br/></li><br/><li id="7">How much time did the majority of 19 to 25-year-olds spend on the telephone each week?<ol class="answerList"><li><a id="q19" >less than 1 hour</a></li><li><a id="q20" >1 to 3 hours</a></li><li><a id="q21" >more than 5 hours</a></li></ol><br/></li><br/><li id="8">Which age group spent the least time on the telephone per week?<ol class="answerList"><li><a id="q22" >12-18</a></li><li><a id="q23" >26-45</a></li><li><a id="q24" >65+</a></li></ol><br/></li><br/><li id="9">How many languages were spoken in 1500?<ol class="answerList"><li><a id="q25" >approximately 7,000</a></li><li><a id="q26" >7,000</a></li><li><a id="q27" >approximately 9,000</a></li></ol><br/></li><br/><li id="10">What is the predicted world population in 2100?<ol class="answerList"><li><a id="q28" >8,000 million</a></li><li><a id="q29" >10,000 million</a></li><li><a id="q30" >80,000 million</a></li></ol><br/></li><br/><li id="11">What does this chart show?<ol class="answerList"><li><a id="q31" >the percentage of the population with e-mail and personal web sites</a></li><li><a id="q32" >the percentage of workers who know how to use e-mail and web sites</a></li><li><a id="q33" >the percentage of workers whose employers provide them with e-mail facilities or personal web sites</a></li></ol><br/></li><br/><li id="12">The percentage of UK employees with access to e-mail or web sites (…) between 1997 and 1998.<ol class="answerList"><li><a id="q34" >decreased</a></li><li><a id="q35" >remained the same</a></li><li><a id="q36" >increased</a></li></ol><br/></li></ol>
